# One package (or @group) per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
# Apply with: ./scripts/apply-atomic-provision.sh (or systemd first-boot, see config/systemd/)
# After layering: reboot (bare metal) or wsl --shutdown and relaunch WSL2.
#
# WSL2 imports: rpm-ostree may fail or be limited; trim this file to distrobox (+ fuse3 if needed)
# or set KINOITE_OSTREE_ONLY=1 and use Flatpaks only. See docs/systemd-rpm-ostree-wsl2-claims.md
#
# --- Tier: minimal defaults (safe starting point) ---
distrobox

# --- Tier: daily-driver metal (fonts, VPN, AppImage FUSE, print, scan, peripherals, mesh VPN) ---
# Comment out this block on WSL-only boxes if `rpm-ostree install` errors.
google-noto-emoji-color-fonts
wireguard-tools
fuse3
7zip
cups
cups-filters
system-config-printer
sane-backends
simple-scan
piper
solaar
tailscale
nm-connection-editor
NetworkManager-openvpn
# NetworkManager-openconnect   # enterprise SSL VPN (OpenConnect); uncomment if needed
libratbag-ratbagd
blueman

# --- Tier: CJK fonts (large download; uncomment if you use East Asian locales) ---
# google-noto-sans-cjk-fonts

# --- Tier: shells / editors (uncomment) ---
# fish
# zsh
# helix
# neovim

# --- Tier: dictionaries ---
# cracklib-dicts

# --- Tier: input methods — pick IBus and/or Fcitx5 stack; match docs/input-and-ime.md ---
# ibus
# ibus-gtk4
# fcitx5
# fcitx5-configtool
# fcitx5-gtk

# --- Tier: power management (laptop; test one approach) ---
# tlp
# tlp-rdw
# auto-cpufreq

# --- Tier: virtualization (KVM users on metal) ---
# libvirt
# virt-manager

# --- Tier: codecs / third-party repos (legal/policy — optional RPM Fusion free) ---
# After enabling rpmfusion-free from Fedora docs, uncomment e.g.:
# ffmpeg

# --- Tier: gaming / 32-bit (Steam from rpm — heavy; Flatpak Steam preferred in gaming.list) ---
# steam

# WSL2: many of the above are irrelevant or fail; prefer Flatpak + distrobox. Edit before apply.
